reviews.review_text: Excellent experience overall. Small and interesting wine list and amazing cocktails. Sat at the bar and the bar team was very engaging and make the experience great.  The food was excellent, excellent technique, presentation and flavours all around. Excited to come back soon!

A gastronomic delight! We celebrated my mother s birthday at AnnaLena on 23/08/2023 and they exceeded our expectations on all fronts. The tasting menu was phenomenal with each course so meticulously thought out and carefully executed. The service was brilliantly orchestrated like clockwork. We commend our server, Arianna, who took the time to take photos for us to celebrate a milestone birthday. Overall, outstanding! Michelin star deserved! Dietary restrictions: They made arrangements for my lactose intolerance.

120% worth it. There is a reason why it s so hard to land a booking here and it shows. From the Michelin worthy service and decor so the presentation of the food. This place was hitting bangers from start to finish. Totally worth coming here for their ever changing menu. Nothing on the menu disappointed. From the tartare to the oysters to the bread and the salmon and the hen.

Perhaps the best dining experience I ve ever had. I tried another Michelin star restaurant in the area and it wasn t at the same level as AnnaLena. Everything was amazing and they accommodated my preference to avoid shellfish.

One of the top restaurants in Vancouver. Great food, service and atmosphere. The reservation is hard to get and it s a bit pricey but you get what you paid for. We did wine pairing on our visit and discovered a few great wines. The only downside the wine portions were quite small for the price and also additional caviar was not worth the price. Overall highly recommended to get there at least once.

Great food and impeccable service. The wow factor was the oysters and the mussels soup was amazing. The only dish that felt underwhelming was the salmon dish (We thought the sauce didnt showcase how good the salmon was). I would definitely recommend the place. Food

Definitely did not disappoint. Service was top notch and food was great. I enjoyed their al a cart better when they offered it before they got the Michelin star, but still awesome. Hopefully they bring back the al a cart menu sometime :)

Excellent service, incredible food, and well informed staff, all while seeming proper yet not snobby, AnnaLena had it all. The tasting menu was phenomenal, and I was sad the torn bread wasn t on the menu. But the Brick Bread felt eerily similar and by far the best dish. Everything was incredible, and the mini surprise bites in between were all delicious. The service  was outstanding. An incredibly well informed sommelier and servers that were kind and genuine, everyone was on their A game. Probably my favorite restaurant in the city

Can t say enough good things about AnnaLena! It s tough to get a res but it s worth it for a special occasion. Every bite was incredible but my favorite was probably the duck with the bread or the seared scallop. The service was perfect too.

Backed by its 2022 Michelin Star, Anna Lenas reputation as an upscale restaurant delivers expectations. The restaurant exclusively offers a meticulously crafted tasting menu that rotates on a fairly frequent basis. Each course will be sure to showcase local ingredients as well as highlight the importance of seasonal flavours. For the connoisseurs, the optional wine pairing will feature carefully selected bottles from all around the world. One thing to note is that securing a table here is akin to winning a gastronomic lottery. Miss the 30 day prior 9am table reservation window and youll find yourself on the waitlist instead.

The food and service was amazing. Very delicate servings on the tasting menu. All dishes were delicate, inspiring and just about the right size, so that we didnt get overstuffed and didnt leave hungry. Wine pairings were very interesting and delicious as well with both local and overseas wines. Our only complaint is the noise level in this place. A little bit of acoustic regulation of the high concrete ceiling would help a lot.

This is a wonderful restaurant located on West 1st, close to the beach, and a wine store next door. Very awesome space, the food and service definitely match up to it. It s one of the Michelin star restaurants in Vancouver and it s definitely earned its reputation. The food was absolutely delicious and carefully crafted. Every bite was perfect and everything just seemed to work well. The cocktails were also delicious and matched well with the dishes. The dessert was fresh and gave a palette cleansing experience - definitely another highlight from an already amazing dinner. If you re worried about being hungry after the tasting menu, you won t be. It definitely will fill you. I don t think you even need to opt for the add ons, but I found it filling. Don t worry about parking either as there is plenty of paid parking in the area. We got lucky and found one right outside the restaurant but cars come and go quite often enough. I would highly recommend coming here, but book well in advance as they fill up quickly.

This is our third time to AnnaLena in the past few years and we werent disappointed. The food, service and ambiance were teriffic. The music was too loud at one point and the manager was kind enough to turn it down. This place is pricy, but a worthwhile experience. If $200 per person (including wine pairing) is too much to swallow, think about skipping one normal dinner and and combining that $$$ into a night at AnnaLena. You will not regret it!

The first time I have visited AnnaLena and I can say it truly deserves the Michelin start that it got last November. The servers are extremely knowledgable about their menu, and their memory is impeccable. Every dish was served in unison and the balance of flavours is perfect with every dish. There was not a single dish we did not like but the torn bread was definitely the highlight of the night. All of us left satisfied and full (rare for a restaurant like this). 5-stars for a 5-star restaurant

A fabulous experience, from food to service. We added the tuna belly and wagyu courses to our tasting menu. Absolutely delicious. I also had the wine pairing. Fantastic pairings. The service was impeccable. Relaxed and personable. I love the layout of the restaurant. All in all amazing time at Annalena.
A stellar restaurant highlighted by spectacular and creative food with local ingredients. Frequent menu changes means new experiences with each visit

Phenomenal course design. If Christopher Nolan were a Chef, it d be like AnnaLena.  Thoroughly enjoyed every component. The wine pairings were meticulously curated. Such hospitality experts as a whole team there. Our server Emma was professional with precise communication skills; It was my first time clearly understanding food/wine descriptions spoken by servers. I loved that a lot of dishes conflated French classics and  Chinese cuisines  which you don t see very often. i.e) Marinated cucumber with duck breasts, scallops with xo sauce.

We were at AnnaLena during Chapter 63. Super attentive service. The food was creative and had well-balanced flavours. There were interesting decorative bits reminisce of the 90s. We could only get bar seats, and the corner we sat was kinda dark. We couldnt see the dishes clearly or take good pics of it. Thankfully, our taste buds could still savour them. Recommended!

Michelin Star! This is our second time eating here. It never seems to disappoint. It s a set menu, their menu changes frequently depending on seasonal ingredients available. Two items that stay fairly frequent is their house made bread! So delicious so flaky dipped into their soup! And their famous oysters with shaved jalapeno foie gras on top. It s just melts in your mouth! Once you ve tasted this, there will be no other oysters that can compare. They only serve one so we ordered another (if they had extras they will serve it)
We had a fantastic meal at AnnaLena. The service was impeccable. The cocktails, wine and five courses were absolutely delicious.

An exquisite dining experience with amazing flavours and brilliant dishes. AnnaLena is at the top of the Vancouver dining experiences. The tasting menu is carefully thought out and it s a pleasure to see the chefs notes as the concept for each tasting menu comes about. The menu unfolds thoughtfully without the dishes competing for one another. Excellent flavours that weee well balanced.  Favourites included the oyster with food grad snow and the spot prawn and mussels. Absolutely decadent. The drinks were fantastic and delicious. The wine pairing is well thought out and ensured each pairing goes well with the course. Overall amazing experience
The best tasting menu I ve tried in Vancouver so far. Every dish was perfect, seamless and balanced. Each ingredient had purpose and the dessert was amazing.

Had an exceptional time. Food came out like clockwork without making you feel rushed between courses. Staff was delightful and knowledgeable. I appreciated how they made the dining experience feel accessible to everyone and not gatekept with industry jargon that might not have been understood by all at the table. Food was beautiful and delicious.  I look forward to coming again and trying a new menu chapter with them in the future.

We had an amazing experience at Anna Lena - the service and cuisine was exceptional! We found the environment fun and relaxed, sitting at the bar and enjoying cocktails provided a special impression. Anna Lena makes a conscious effort to source ingredients locally, I wont get into each individual dish but Anna Lena is worth checking out - recommend you place your name on the waitlist as last minute spots do open up. Thank you to the team at Anna Lena, we left quite full from some of the best food we had ever enjoyed! The details of everything we were served was carefully considered and extraordinary.

Excellent in every way, from the minute we walked in, the service was extremely attentive, the food was simply amazing, every dish beautifully curated & complimentary, deserving of the Michelin star, absolutely world class. Dietary restrictions: Catered very well for gluten feee

Outstanding dinner experience with the February 21st tasting menu! Gastronomically impeccable with many different flavors, textures and ingredients. They were even able to accommodate my father s cheese allergy on a very short notice. Looking forward to trying the next menu!

Absolutely delicious.  The service was dead on. Our server McKenna gave perfect recommendations for wine to pair with the meal and was super nice and knowledgeable.  The tasting menu (chapter 67) was delightful, the highlight for me was the mussel dish with torn bread.  Great night!

I visited and AnnaLena for a birthday dinner over a month ago. It was an incredible meal with friendly service and food that came out promptly one dish after another. The highlights of the meal were the deconstructed lasagna dish which was astonishingly delicious and the torn bread dish. The staff clean the bread crumbs off your table, fold your napkin for you when you step away from the table, and change cutlery after almost every dish. Service feels attentive, but not too intrusive. Some of the staff were a little awkward, but so am I so who am I to complain. This restaurant is certainly worthy of its Michelin star. My only complaint is that the table set up is rather close for a few of the tables. For example, when the staff are having a conversation with the patrons at another table, I regrettably had a butt in my face while I was eating. This is a minor gripe that didn t get in the way of an otherwise great meal. AnnaLena was wonderful, I would come again most certainly as the menu continues to change.

One the finest restaurants in Canada. The food is just straight up delicious and very creative. Service is very personable and the restaurant is filled all kinds of cool little touches like the MJ figure above the kitchen.

Fantastic dinner. We really enjoyed their tasting menu (apparently they are switching the menu very soon, so we hope to return soon), and their service was great. From the photos, I actually wasnt really convinced it would be a nice place to go; the food and interior looked pretty basic to me, but I was wrong. I still feel that they could get more unique looking or interesting plates etc., but their food was  original and they tasted fantastic! It is a pricier restaurant, but its worth it. If you are in the area and would like to try out a great restaurant, I highly recommend this place. One thing I suggest is, there were a couple dishes you were encouraged to eat with your fingers, it would have been nice to have a wet towel or a finger bowl to clean your fingers afterwards. Thank you for a great dinner experience.

Set tasting menu with a huge drink option available. Had a wonderful experience here. The service was friendly and excellent, the food was fabulous and the atmosphere/ambience  was impeccable. Not kid friendly, although they provide options outside their tasting menu for kids, I would advise against bringing kids. Definitely the place to go with your significant other or a few friends to enjoy a slow non rushed dinner while having intimate conversations. Would definitely come back here. Each of the items in the five course is well balanced in taste with a little bit more on the savoury side (except for dessert). I especially enjoyed the mussels.
Chapter 64. The best dinner experience ever in Vancouver. :) Food was amazing and also service was great. Thanks to Jeff and Esme.

Mind-blowing experience with an ultimate chefs tasting menu. The service was top notch and the ambiance was perfect. Every course (including ones not listed) were some of the best bites Ive ever had. Highly recommend this to anyone interest in fine dining. Absolutely deserving of their Michelin star!

The tasting menu is beyond amazing. Leaving the menu to the chef allows you to try new dishes and ingredients you would never think about trying. We loved every single dish we were served even though we probably wouldn t order that on a regular menu. The portion sizes are small but throughout the entire course it s actually very filling! Would HIGHLY recommend this for anyone feeling adventurous or just wanting a great place to dine!

We visited AnnaLena for Chapter Fifty Two and had the most amazing time. Every dish was prepared with care and tasted divine. I d recommend getting the wine pairing to enhance your experience. And the torn bread is to die for!!! This an excellent place to celebrate a special occasion. 100% recommend.

My girlfriend and I had the tasting menu which was about $95/ person. We absolutely enjoyed the meals and the service. We learned that the menu is changed about every 6 weeks. Getting a reservation can be quite tough and you have to book a month out, we were lucky to be able to book last minute but highly recommend booking in advance.

We were in love with every single dish. The cocktails were perfect, the recommended wine was beautiful. One of us is vegetarian and we had called ahead and informed them of some allergies as well and they were more than happy to accommodate dietary restrictions!

My favorite place to eat in Vancouver. I ve been there 7 times in the last 2 years and every experience has been spectacular. Their wine pairing is always very inspired so if you can drink, definitely go all in. Cannot say enough what a great place they are!

This restaurant is an absolute gem! From the moment I stepped inside, I was greeted with warm hospitality. The ambiance was charming and inviting. The menu was a culinary delight, offering an impressive array of mouthwatering dishes. Each bite was bursting with flavor, and the presentation was top-notch. The attentive staff made the dining experience even more enjoyable. Whether it was a scrumptious starter, a delectable main course, or a delightful dessert, everything surpassed my expectations. I left with a satisfied palate and cant wait to return. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a truly unforgettable dining experience!

Used to come here a couple of times a year, but this is our first time back since they started offering set menus.  Amazing bites as I remembered!  Thoroughly enjoyed everything dishes are creative, flavours are on point, with just the right amount of salt and acid, beautiful plating, and good flow for a tasting menu.  We missed the torn bread a lot, so glad it was on the menu tonight!  And the sticky toffee pudding was so delicious too, such an amazing way to end the meal!  Will definitely be back regularly again!
Damnnnnnn 10/10 So satisfying from the interior design to the music, service, and of course the food. Would love to come back! Hip & unpretentious BUT still manages to retain all the fine details

Just had one of the most fabulous meals here for DOV! They offer an amazing 5 course tasting menu. Each dish is very well composed, all the flavours work so well together & the presentation is beautiful. As each course is served, they explained in detail the components of the dish. The service is impeccable! They are friendly & knowledgeable. The ambiance is relaxed & the decor is eclectic. This by far has got to be not only one of the best DOV experiences Ive ever had, but also one of the best meals Ive had. Anna Lena knows what theyre doing & they are doing it oh so well. We will definitely be back & I highly recommend you check them out! @inspiringfoodie

This restaurant introduced the multi course tasting menu and has consistently been rating as one of the top 100 restaurants in Canada..our decision to try this very interesting approach was made as other friends just raved about their experience and our choice was awarded with a top flight dining exposure to the chef s focus on local farm seasonal items and creative evolvement of the ingredients ..the staff are welcoming and very well informed in all aspects of the dining experience and it was a pleasure to listen and interact with everyone as each course was presented.. a totally delightful evening and the food was superb..and so here we are once again with our waiter Scott providing very helpful information on the tasting menu and the accompanying wine tasting that we chose..this restaurant is so special, the staff are friendly and attentive and the service was exceptional..thank you again Scott for your attention to detail and for the  very helpful information on the wines we tasted..we will be back soon, probably for my birthday in December..and here is my Birthday and the evening was Devine ! so once again we celebrate our birthday at this fabulous restaurant and totally enjoy ourselves with the imaginative cuisine and the entertainment so here we are again celebrating a special anniversary with our very favourite restaurant in Vancouver and this dinner was amazing..the service was fantastic and very authentic..conversations with the staff made our time in this restaurant feel like a home meal with special friends..our night here led to a wonderful evening before, during and after our dinner meal..AnnaLena is a treasure to experience with the imaginative cuisine and culinary specialties

We first dined here was about two months ago and had a fantastic dinner. To make sure it wasnt just a one-time lucky experience I wanted to try it again before leaving a review. Yesterday, we brought our son and girlfriend here to celebrate his birthday and we werent disappointed. Every course was thoughtfully prepared with every element playing a crucial part of the overall dish. The food was absolutely top notch and the presentation was lovely. Our son had just eaten at his favourite restaurant the night before and came to the conclusion that AnnaLena was now his new favourite! The service was phenomenal. We had Rebekah as our host previously and this time we had Tara. They were both excellent at making us feel welcomed and really enhanced the dining experience with their descriptions of each dish and expansive knowledge of the wine pairings. You can really feel that the staff are passionate about the food and wine and really want you to get the most out of your time here. For me, AnnaLena is my favourite tasting menu restaurant in Vancouver. I love being surprised at what a restaurant decides to present to its diners, and Chef Robbinss use of ingredients, flavours and textures continues to impress. I can hardly wait for my next visit!
Had a great time trying out their new tasting menu. The service is so friendly and efficient. Each wine pairing came with an interesting explanation! The torn bread is so delicious.

Went for the tasting menu course. The staff was very pleasant and attentive with all the coming and going of plates  etc. Expect a LONG wait between each course. The restaurant was not fully packed when we were there, but for some reason the food took easily 20 min between each course.

AMAZING! ive wanted to try this restaurant for quite a while and ended up finally dragging two very reluctant friends with me. all three of us left having had the best meals of our lives! the drink pairing fit perfectly with the dishes and highly recommend it! the atmosphere is relaxing and friendly and very comfortable. all the workers were so nice and made us feel very welcome. i am going to be recommending this restaurant to anyone who will listen!

Amazing!!! I used to come often when I worked in the area, pre pandemic, but havent visited since. Celebrated my birthday here,  and was still blown away by every menu item. Presentation, taste, creativity, execution, all on point, which is extremely difficult to do with set menus of all different tastes and texture. Again... amazing.

We really enjoyed the tasting menu we had at AnnaLena. Such a thoughtful menu and the flavours builds up and gets more intense after each dish. My faves were the trout, tortellini and the duck - the duck was perfectly cooked and so tender. The dessert was just the right sweetness and was the perfect end to the meal. If you re not into alcoholic drinks, the From East End to West End mocktail was refreshing. The service was also great. Highly recommend this restaurant.
Fantastic, everyone and everything was amazing. Must dine here,you wont be disappointed!

Update November 13, 2022: When dining at a restaurant, there are generally three things I look for: quality of food, service and ambiance.  There are so many restaurants in Vancouver that have one or more of those things. They might have good food but horrible service. Or they are really nice people but the food is average. There are some places that have ok food, service and ambiance but don t reach the level of excellence. AnnaLena has amazing food, excellent service and a nice ambiance. They are gracious and not pretentious like a few other places in town. And after coming back multiple times throughout the years I know for a fact that they are also consistent. I know that whenever I dine at AnnaLena the experience will be amazing. Food was delicious, cocktails were delicious, I was very satisfied. And the set menu is a relative bargain for a Michelin starred restaurant. The only nitpick I have this time is that they covered their beautiful pasta dish with foam. The pasta underneath is beautiful (based on their IG pics) so it was a shame that we could not see it. Update Nov 21, 2021: Still a great experience! Original Review: One of my favourite restaurants in Vancouver and one I constantly return to. I love their new tasting menu format which means that whenever I go it is a new experience. Regardless of what the food is, the execution is always top notch. Taste and presentation are excellent and it is really good value for the price too. Anna Lena is a must visit restaurant in Vancouver.

I have been lucky to eat at Anna Lena numerous times including spending New years here one year. Every time it is excellent, the service is always top notch with excellent wine recommendations. The food is always creative and showcases amazing local produce. Definitely one of my favorites in Vancouver

Outstanding service, food, cocktails. Vibe is buzzy and packed the night we dined there. Favorite for two of us was the amazing foie gras first course. Dishes were creative and beautiful. The kitchen seems tight and well organized. A lovely evening!

They change their tasting menu every four weeks. If you have never been here, you should at least try one time. Foods are yummy. Atmosphere here is good. Me and my friends were really having a good time here.

This place has an amazing tasting menu!! Compared to other places, $75 for this menu felt like a steal. They give good portion sizes, leaving you full, but not overly stuffed. Every dish looked and tasted great, I was impressed. This is a great place to celebrate a special occasion of just have a great dining experience in a more intimate setting. Service was great and I d recommend people to come here, it s one of those hidden gems that s worth a long drive to get to.

Amazing, delicious and great service! Recently went for dinner with my husband. This was our first time after they got recognized with a Michelin star. Everything is still amazing and has not disappointed me yet. Highlights are always the torn bread, mussels and the pasta. Definitely splurge on the wine pairing!

One of the best fine dining in Vancouver. I ordered a tasting menu which changes every week. All food tasted great, was well presented and a fair amount of portion was provided. Server explained each menu and was very friendly. A table was not close to the other tables in the patio, which helps with some social distancing while eating. I am definitely going back for the next special occasion.

From the beginning, to the end, it s a complete journey. A story that I would love to revisit a thousand times. I see why they have their first Michelin star. I was going to make another phone call if they didn t have it by now. I would definitely say take the ride if you haven t already. Can t wait to revisit Vancouver again just to revisit this dream. Excellent service, food, and drinks. A complete story that takes your pallet on a once in a life trip.  Please excuse brevity and typos as this review was sent from my smartphone.

The vegetable tasting menu and wine pairing are so well designed and executed. The food and drinks were delicious individually, but paired together they were elevated to another level. The service was exceptional as well. The explanation for each wine pairing was detailed and each had a story to tell. We had a lovely experience.  I would recommend this restaurant.

I come back to this place every month now. This month they have the dine out menu which I think is great. For a bit less price you get the same quality of food. You only lose one pasta course which honestly I dont care about that much. Overall I like their salad course the best, it is almost always my favorite. They use fresh, seasonal ingredients and make them tasty. Other courses are also good. Appetizers are always innovative. This time they had a shaved Foie Gras, it was impressive. Dessert is never too sweet or too big, leaves a refreshing note. My only suggestion for this place is to improve their fish main course. I got fish twice, once it was overcooked and dry, the 2nd time it was kind of flavorless. This time I got the port belly and it was amazing. Didnt taste oily and stinky at all. Service is also very attentive, they always come by to refill my water. Decor is morden, owner really likes KAWS, and have a good taste in music.

absolutely would recommend annalena to any of my friends! beautiful atmosphere and very friendly staff. the prix fixe changes every month and is exceptionally delicious. the flavor pairings are well thought out and presentation is gorgeous. the pictures posted were for the june 2022 menu. the spaghettini with bacon foam and morel mushrooms was definitely one of my favorites. i can t wait to return!

Michillen star restaurants have it for a reason - exceptional service. The atmosphere could get more cozy, but the lighting was good, the food was fabulous, the quantity was just the right amount and the location is set in a quiet neighborhood. Overall an impressive experience. Recommended.

WOW, Just   delicious. My husband and I came here for our 10 000 day anniversary.  We had a six course tasting menu and wine pairings. The food was phenomenal. Great progression and portion sizes. Food was beautiful and tasty. Lots of creamy, salty, crunchy, umami flavours. The ahi foie gras and the agnolotti were some favourites. Torn bread was very good. But everything was great. The service was attentive, friendly, and spot on. Anna Lena definitely exceeded all our expectations. One of my new favorite   restaurants. Also the cherry biscuit at the end of the meal. Amazing!!!

There is no other restaurant in the lower mainland that does such a consistently unreal service. The people, food, cocktails and wine offerings are always spot on. The staff are passionate and so knowledgeable. We try to come every few months, sometimes make it in more often. They switch the menu every six weeks but I don t even care if I eat the same menu twice, that s how delicious every course is.

Great experience! All food was perfectly detailed and handled with care. Menu was chapter 65 which was great and refreshing from other places I ve dined. The dessert blew me away though, it was so delicious. Food : 5/5

The restaurant is small with a chic vibe. Each dish in the tasting menu are interesting and build the flavour on top of each other. Really enjoyed the food and the experience! The only regret is that we didn t get their house made bread, we are definitely going back!

My experience at Anna Lena stands out to me as the best dining experience I ve ever had. Yes, it is fine dining. But the staff and the space welcomes you in, no matter who you are. The atmosphere in the space radiates as it is filled with pop culture decor and hip hop & r&b music - which I loved it s not everyday you dine in a restaurant space like that. I felt as if I was in someone s home! The food being delicious is a no brainer. It was truly a culinary experience. Thank you for making my birthday dinner special. I will be back! And I have already been telling all my friends about my experience.

Exquisite tasting menu experience, exploring various pasta oriented flavors when we went. Their menu is frequently updated, currently every 2-3 weeks approximately. Ours was a very strong price/value offer with 6 different courses plus dessert for $68pp. The price will vary with what is being offered and in season. Staff was extremely friendly and knowledgeable about everything, offering us great options pair our individual drink preferences with each course / the entire meal if you prefer to keep it simpler. Will be back for sure.

Second time dining here, first time since michelin star. Of all the michelin awarded restaurants we ve been to, this one I felt truly deserved it. The savoury courses were all exceptional and innovative to warrant a star. The only mediocre dish was the dessert.. plum, hazelnut, thyme ice cream. Service was personal and excellent. We all enjoyed the meal and look forward to future chapters!

We had the Valentines set menu and it was amazing. I had the fresh oysters, Dungeness crab, squash ravioli, bison, and a sorbet dessert. Everything was beautiful and tasted as good as it looked. Our server, Michael, was attentive and funny and gracious. The restaurant was also super accommodating of my dietary restrictions. Usually the modified dishes are subpar compared to the original dishes, but in this case there was extreme care put into the modified dishes and they were absolutely delicious. Thank you for the lovely dining experience on a special  day. We will definitely be returning :)
Great food and impeccable service. We had a really lovely dinner.

(For dining sept 2nd) This was the best meal Ive ever had.   Each course was delicious and something I would order a la carte. The service is what really puts this restaurant on another level. The staff are military-like in their timing and precision but not their disposition, as our server had a dry sense of humour that mirrors mine closely. Unfortunately I cant remember her name, but I feel like in another life we could be friends. Its one of the most expensive meals Ive had but worth every penny for this culinary experience. The only aspect of anna lena that is close to a downside would be the acoustics in the building, it was sometimes difficult to hear our server. Also, the cocktails are up there with the best cocktail bars around, very well balanced. Disregard my recommendation at your peril!

With physical distancing AnnaLena has temporarily halted their regular menu and introduced a tasting menu-only menu that changes every week. I went last night and it was great. Start to finish, the service was great, the food was creative and most importantly it was delicious. They didn t hold back on their delivery and the small details really brought their dishes together. The only negative is parking can be difficult in the summer because of its proximity to Kits beach.
Great service and decent pricing. The dishes really hit the mark for us. Don t forget to give the yummy cocktails a try.

First time being back since COVID and had the (slightly modified) greatest hits set menu for the Visa Infinite dinner. Great wines, even better food. Miss coming here for cocktails after the fireworks.

Amazing restaurant tucked away on 1st. Great service from the moment you walk in, with attentive care throughout your meal. The dishes are all meant to be shared, so make sure you ask if youre not sure about the size. We got the torn bread, duck pate, bison tartare, octopus, mussels, and scallops. Definitely an amazing Vancouver meal, with the seafood really shining through. The octopus was my favourite dish, tenderly cooked with a smokey tint, alongside potatoes and horseradish. I was impressed by everything we ordered and would rate this restaurant as one of the best in Vancouver.

A fantastic evening start to finish! For our anniversary dinner we chose AnnaLena, and are so glad we did. Was hard to get a table, so book in advance. We came in at 5:15, which was early, but so worth it. We chose the tasting menu, which was full of highlights. The halibut was a revelation all by itself. Every dish had its own perspective and complimented the next. Service was great, management was very engaged in the overall experience. We definitely felt cared for and were very happy when we left. Looking forward to our next visit.

The Amuse Bouche and desert were the best of the meal along with the wine pairing. Mussels with torn bread wonderful. Unfortunately, the flavor of the salmon was a little smothered by the sauce. The service was again excellent.

Great service....although finding waiters who can explain a dish talking through a facemask is rare....what was that you just mumbled? Besides that, the other complaints were: small portions in the tasting menu....i know its a tasting menu but when its so good, is it wrong to want seconds? And where we were seated, close to the corner entrance, my partner kept feeling the breath and could smell the sweat from the fitness goers coming down the stairs from the adjacent Ron Zalko fitness studio. Pick your seat with caution. Big pluses for a great menu, wonderful creative foods, great presentation, lovely dishware, attentive service and big customer service kudos to them for accepting an expired gift certificate with no hesitation. Thats excellent customer service in my books. Oh last critisism: the dessert of cherries with ice cream was anti-climatic and too basic compared to the rest of the intricate preceeding menu. You must visit at least once. Parking is sometimes difficult so go early.

Torn Bread. Torn Bread. I cannot stress that enough! It s on their  secret menu . The food and service here is always amazing, and I love the rotating tasting menu. I think I have come here enough times now to make a proper review! The only downside is the noise level. I went as a party of 4 and could not even hear anyone at the table, nor the server as she was describing the dishes. If you re seated in the booths, the sound echoes on the inside of the arch. Not sure if the group of ladies seated in the other booth were loud, drunk, or just  loud, but we heard their entire conversation all evening. TLDR. Ask for seating by the windows, where it s tucked away for a quieter dining experience. Do not sit at the booths.

Dined at the bar last night by myself.  Well worth the Michelin star. The tasting menu was amazing. I think the king salmon course was my favourite.  I had the add on bluefin and the add on wyagu.  I would recommend both. The platewear and ceramics were also beautiful. Service was excellent Tyler went above and beyond..  He also made me 3 mocktails which were his creations and not on the menu.  All were fantastic, especially the one which had basil and cucumber. When I asked about the ceramics I was given a page which lists the ceramics makers and some details about them.  Even the paper it was printed on was beautiful. I will come back and dine with my partner next time we come to Vancouver. Also, check out the wall display on the way to the restrooms.  The small lego figures made me smile.  A little whimsy at one of the best restaurants in the country.  May The Force be with you.

One of my new favourite restaurants.  Their oysters are the best I ve had and I would come back just for those.  Their muscles and duck were good - you can see the attention to detail in every plate.  The staff were attentive but laid back; atmosphere was lively.  The table next to us had the tasting menu which looked great with generous portion sizes - would definitely come back to try that.  Overall, high end food and staff without the pretentious feeling.

Oh man this place was amazing, the food was honestly super delicious, every course was so well thought out and every bite was to die for. We got cocktails as well and they were also very well mixed and tasted delightful. Yea the tasting menu is a bit pricey, but it s worth to visit this place at least once.

Beyond 5 stars for Annalena. Food was incredible, the bluefin tuna add on was definitely a highlight. Wine pairings were also extremely thought out and unique to the experience. Shoutout to Rev (mind my spelling if it s incorrect) for her amazing service - she was passionate and funny and made the experience comfortable and fun. Can t wait to see what they come up in the next tasting menu!

This is my second time at AnnaLena and both times they did not disappoint! The vibe is trendy yet inviting and the food is decadent yet light and fresh. The cocktails are on the lighter side with unexpected notes but works really well. Make sure to get their torn bread and fried chicken.

Ive been here 6 times now. Each time really good - we recommend it to all our friends. And it keeps getting better - our last tasting menu was one of the best meals weve ever had. The new kitchen Chef added a new level of refinement to Anna Lena. Were avid foodies and the only better meal weve had was at Alinea in Chicago - one of the best restaurants in the world. p.s.: Vegetarians delight, they do amazing dishes for us!

Amazing. Came here for my wedding anniversary The service was exceptional The food Even better. If you come here - and you should - get the wine pairing instead of a single bottle. Matched to perfection
Phenomenal experience! Chapter 65 was amazing from start to finish. Service at the bar from Nick was delightful. We enjoyed the wine pairing. Thoughtfully executed and impeccably presented 10/10!
Definitely worth trying to snag a reservation. Even the food that I dont like for personal tastes was delicious. The service crew were all great. Will definitely return.

Amazing food, outstanding service. We were 2 and as suggested by the staff, we ordered 4 dishes - bread, squid, scallop and grains, the latter our favourite. Also tried the chocolate dessert, love the different textures and flavours. All dishes were beautifully presented. Servers were always checking water, made sure the table was always clean and replaced plates and cutlery before bringing a new dish. Thanks for all staff who made our experience so good!
Creative food, good use of textures and those sauces! Keep doing what youre doing as it was delicious. I think portion sizes were just right too.

Annalena is exceptional every time. The wonderful people who works there are always knowledgeable, and create a special curated experience. This restaurant serves amazing west coast/ fusion inspired fine dining that does not disappoint. I truly hope they survive through this surreal time as the people who work there are all superstars at what they do! I look forward to many more dining experiences at this premiere Vancouver restaurant. This a great example of a wonderful Vancouver fine dining experience we should all support! Extraordinary plated food that is rich in flavour and presentation! Super special staff! Excellent cocktail and wine menu!

Place looks amazing Love the lego storm troopers it made my day Bread was so soft, crispy and flavorful and the homemade butter was delicious Fried chicken was great as was the pasta (best part from the pasta was the kale, other than that it was just basic). Ended the night with the fried chicken skin covered in chocolate. It was interesting Service was outstanding from everyone who made contact with us. Didnt wait more than 3 to 5 minutes for anything. Timing of each course was excellent

The food here is amazing. Once in awhile, we always come back here. The mussels with torn bread is a must to order. The beef flank is great too. Once in awhile one or two dishes will change according to the season. I will highly recommend for anyone visiting Vancouver to try out this restaurant.

We went to AnnaLena for dine out. Atmosphere was cozy and inviting. Our server was attentive and charming. The best part was the food. It was quite an experience for my palate. The food was prepared with intricacy and passion. Exceeded my expectations.

Anna Lena is simply incredible. Just a beautiful experience, as soon as you walk through through the door, you feel the elegance, sophistication, the wow factor. This place has chic interior decor. Incredible staff, professional, attentive and extremely caring. There s really no way to describe how good the food was other than to say it s the epitome of gastronomical experience. Brovo!
Shocked they only got one star. Omg this is soooooooooo goooooood

Excellent tasting menu, which was a selection of dishes (6 courses) from the regular menu in smaller plates. A great way to try a little of everything, but if I were to do it again, I would order from their regular menu. We started with the Oyster, it was fresh, a little spicy (jalapeno mignonette) with shaved foie gras and a great way to start the evening. The next was the greens, which consisted of chickpea panisse and tahini. It was surprisingly delicious! All the flavours balanced well and the miso eggplant on the bottom gave it a great flavour. The next was an amazing mussels in a creamy sauce with mushrooms and a hint of lemongrass. I had every drop, dipping my torn bread to soak up the last bits. Getting to bigger dishes, we had the crunchy buttery fried chicken next and then the best dish of the night, the sablefish. I loved everything about the sablefish. It was served with a base of creamy mashed potatoes, the pickled shitake gave he dish a good kick, but it didnt take away from the fish, which was cooked beautifully, with that crispy skin and flaky meat.  We ended the mains with beef bavette. Only complaints about the meal: the beef was actually the poorest of the dishes that night. Although it was a good dish, that, and the blood orange serbert dessert was a let down from the amazing mussels and sablefish. I would have liked dinner to end stronger, with their best dish. This was almost enough for me to give 4*, but the attentive and friendly service we received throughout the night made up for it. The other complaint is the wait between meals. The couple who came in after us also had a tasting menu. They started while we were on our third course and by the end, they had caught up which tells you we had been waiting a very long time in between courses (especially between the fish and the beef) TL,DR: All in all, a great meal - but skip the tasting menu. Order the greens, mussels and sablefish. The plates are meant to share, family style. AnnaLena is lively, and can get quite noisy. The decor is quite interesting with Kaws bears throughout.

Been wanting to come to this restaurant for the longest time. Tried to walk-in to grab a table but quickly found out that you have to reserve online. We ordered the mussels, chicken, pasta, steak, bread and of course their chocolate covered chicken skin. Everything was cooked to perfection and seasoning was . The dishes of the night have to be the mussels off-the-shell and the pasta. The chocolate covered chicken skin is interesting and worth a try! Service was incredibly attentive and friendly. Highly recommended! Also, be aware of their cancellation policy as they will charge a cancellation fee of $25 per guest.

Came here to check out  Chapter Sixty Five  of their set tasting menu. Overall, it was a great experience. The food was delicious and the cocktails were great. The A5 wagyu skewers, Hokkaido scallops, garlic torn bread and even the tomato salad with the creamy dill dressing were standouts. Only let down was the glazed cherry and thyme ice cream dessert, but that s only because I m not a big fan of the cherries and the thyme ice cream tasted like a big pile of Cajun chicken. The interior decor was a nice blend of contemporary designs mixed with streetwear culture pieces. Staff were attentive, engaging and friendly. Only other knock is a mixup with the host staff, as there was some confusion. We had checked in, saw that a table for 2 was already set up but we were told that they were still preparing our tables and sent us away, advising us that they would text us when the table was set and to go back later. As we left to walk nearby to kill time, literally within a minute we got a text notifying us that our table was ready - it was the table that we noticed was already set up when we had initially walked in. That little misadventure was pretty unnecessary, but first world problems I suppose. Nonetheless, I would definitely recommend checking this place out.
